# Kung Fu Chess — Core Rules

## Stack

- C++17, STL only, no third-party deps
- Headers in `include/`, sources in `src/`
- Build: `.\build.bat` or CMake

## Language

- **All comments must be in English** — never Hebrew or mixed-language comments
- Identifiers, error strings, and reason codes: English only
- User-facing stdout protocol stays as defined (`ERROR UNKNOWN_TOKEN`, etc.)

## Code style

- **Header vs implementation (strict):** `.h` files are headers only (declarations, include guards, `static constexpr` constants, defaulted members); `.cpp` files hold all function/method bodies — never define function bodies inline in a header
- Include guards: `#ifndef BOARD_H` / `#define BOARD_H` / `#endif`
- Classes: PascalCase (`GameEngine`, `RuleEngine`); methods: camelCase (`requestMove`)
- Structs for plain data (`MoveResult`, `Position`); classes for behavior
- Prefer `const` methods and `const` references for read-only params
- Keep file-local helpers as `static` functions in `.cpp` files

## Domain

- Cell tokens: `"."` empty; `"wK"`, `"bQ"` — color (`w`/`b`) + piece (`KQRBNP`)
- `Position`: `{ row, col }` with `isValid()`; always bounds-check before grid access
- Pixel coords map via `BoardMapper` / `pixelToCell(x, y)` when input layer is used

## Constraints

- When changes affect project structure, architecture, or conventions — update `agents.mdc`, `AGENTS.md`, and relevant `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files
- Minimize diff scope; do not refactor unrelated code
- Do not add tests or docs unless requested
- Do not create git commits unless the user asks
- Register new `.cpp` files in both `build.bat` and `CMakeLists.txt`
